  "body": "# Problem\n\nIn previous releases up to 0.13.0 we were using term 'recovery phrase' for 12 words used to recover an account. In the release 0.14.0 because of re-design some parts of the app use term 'seed phrase' for the same entity. It should be fixed so old users have consistent experience.\n\n## Implementation\n\nPlaces to change seed phrase to recovery phrase:\n1. Account explorer:\n![Screenshot_20190724-120215](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/61785029-25966f80-ae0b-11e9-9ffd-a7e71752b113.png)\n\n2. v1 warning\n![Screenshot_20190724-120250](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/61785094-419a1100-ae0b-11e9-92cd-b6c6d57e63bd.png)\n\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n\"Seed phrase\" term is not shown on any screen in the app. Term \"recovery phrase\" is used instead of \"seed phrase\"",
